WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.230 --> 00:00:23.270
We found Billy's rift.

2
00:00:27.320 --> 00:00:28.740
Tim. is that you?

3
00:00:29.490 --> 00:00:30.950
Tim. do you copy?

4
00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:34.006
I think it's interference from the rift.

5
00:00:34.030 --> 00:00:35.266
What do you think?

6
00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:37.420
Yeah. It must be.

7
00:00:41.330 --> 00:00:42.370
Kei.

8
00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:45.210
Kei.

9
00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:47.920
You all right?

10
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:55.680
I actually believed that
Billy abandoned Hiroshi.

11
00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:00.440
But he was just trying to
put our family back together.

12
00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:03.900
Well. that's because that's who he was.

13
00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.170
- Grand central station.
- Yeah.

14
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:25.436
This must be where titan
x goes back to axis mundi.

15
00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:27.646
Yeah. No. we got the right rift.

16
00:01:27.670 --> 00:01:28.880
Thank you. Billy.

17
00:01:29.670 --> 00:01:32.550
But we just need to figure
out a way to get her here.

18
00:02:08.090 --> 00:02:09.420
Come on. let's go.

19
00:02:20.810 --> 00:02:24.230
And just when you think
it can't get any weirder…

20
00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:26.360
look out!

21
00:02:28.610 --> 00:02:31.070
- You all right?
- Yeah. yeah.

22
00:02:37.660 --> 00:02:39.200
Did you see that?

23
00:02:41.410 --> 00:02:43.120
They weren't even interested in us.

24
00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:46.476
- It was like we're not even here.
- No.

25
00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:48.750
No. they're running
away from something.

26
00:02:49.290 --> 00:02:50.540
Come on. let's go.

27
00:05:03.100 --> 00:05:06.400
Kong and titan x are expendable
if it means I can save dad.

28
00:05:10.020 --> 00:05:12.020
I found her. She's in
the containment vault.

29
00:05:12.810 --> 00:05:13.980
Copy that.

30
00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:17.060
What do you mean. you can "save" him?

31
00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:19.966
Is that what Isabel promised you?

32
00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:22.216
That if you'd help her get to axis mundi.

33
00:05:22.240 --> 00:05:24.926
you can magically go back in time
and stop dad from getting killed?

34
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:26.766
- It wasn't her idea.
- She's using you.

35
00:05:26.790 --> 00:05:29.016
She just wants to go
there to make a profit.

36
00:05:29.040 --> 00:05:30.346
That isn't true.

37
00:05:30.370 --> 00:05:32.146
That's all apex wants!

38
00:05:32.170 --> 00:05:33.380
This is about what I want.

39
00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.360
And if it meant saving dad. I
thought you'd understand too.

40
00:05:46.010 --> 00:05:47.930
But you can't change the past.

41
00:05:49.470 --> 00:05:50.510
All right!

42
00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:52.610
Just take it easy.

43
00:05:58.610 --> 00:06:00.030
The levels are holding steady.

44
00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:03.716
Good. Don't exceed
where Brenda took it.

45
00:06:03.740 --> 00:06:06.256
We need to keep everything
stable until Kong shows up.

46
00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:08.720
With that thing caterwauling
out there. it won't be long now.

47
00:06:16.500 --> 00:06:17.750
Let me out!

48
00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:38.730
Wait.

49
00:06:48.780 --> 00:06:50.370
Where is it coming from?

50
00:06:51.750 --> 00:06:54.800
That's the same chopper they
used to snatch that titan egg with.

51
00:06:57.630 --> 00:07:00.090
That's where that
creature call's coming from.

52
00:07:03.470 --> 00:07:06.946
I don't know what that call
is. but it's likely to attract Kong.

53
00:07:06.970 --> 00:07:07.970
Yeah.

54
00:07:08.600 --> 00:07:11.690
And if the last bearing we got
off of that titan tracker is correct.

55
00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:15.650
it's heading right towards titan x.

56
00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:21.916
I'm worried about Cate and kentaro.

57
00:07:21.940 --> 00:07:23.900
How much farther is this place?

58
00:07:24.440 --> 00:07:26.280
It shouldn't be more
than a couple of klicks.

59
00:07:29.660 --> 00:07:33.726
Well. there was an incident
in the '90s that involved

60
00:07:33.750 --> 00:07:38.550
some skullcrawlers and their
attraction to the smell of sunscreen.

61
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:45.300
Monarch have any other
personnel on the island?

62
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.220
Wait.

63
00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:58.496
- Can't this thing go any faster?
- If there was an actual road.

64
00:07:58.520 --> 00:08:00.456
Do you know how much Kong weighs?

65
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:03.800
Well. I mean. we don't know exactly. but
it's somewhere between 70 and 90.000 tons.

66
00:08:06.030 --> 00:08:07.466
That weighs 90.000 tons?

67
00:08:07.490 --> 00:08:08.886
Geez.

68
00:08:08.910 --> 00:08:10.886
- Please!
- What's the holdup?

69
00:08:10.910 --> 00:08:15.500
…a giant monkey and it's on a
rampage and you guys are so screwed.

70
00:08:16.250 --> 00:08:17.636
Hey. hands. hands. hands.

71
00:08:17.660 --> 00:08:19.476
Put it down. put it down. Hands. hands.

72
00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:21.436
Put it on the dashboard.
on the dashboard.

73
00:08:21.460 --> 00:08:24.000
- Put it on the dash!
- Hey. don't do anything stupid.

74
00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:32.156
You work for Isabel Simmons. right?

75
00:08:32.180 --> 00:08:35.656
I'm just a geology phd with a
hundred grand in student debt.

76
00:08:35.680 --> 00:08:37.930
Isabel's not paying me
enough to take bullets for her.

77
00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:40.640
What do you want?

78
00:08:41.270 --> 00:08:43.730
Well. we're gonna take your ride.

79
00:08:51.950 --> 00:08:54.370
Monarch ground team. come in.

80
00:08:56.290 --> 00:08:58.040
Tim. how do you read? Over.

81
00:09:01.420 --> 00:09:03.186
They're young. and tough and smart.

82
00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:04.340
Most of the time.

83
00:09:13.390 --> 00:09:15.366
Known each other for
two weeks. I look up.

84
00:09:15.390 --> 00:09:18.156
you want to charge down
the beach toward a titan.

85
00:09:18.180 --> 00:09:19.770
You're like two peas in a pod.

86
00:09:26.020 --> 00:09:27.690
Did I miss something important?

87
00:09:30.530 --> 00:09:35.006
Well. after you left suzuki-sensei's place.

88
00:09:35.030 --> 00:09:36.280
Cate and I…

89
00:09:37.580 --> 00:09:39.766
Well. Cate connected with titan x.

90
00:09:39.790 --> 00:09:41.130
Here we go.

91
00:09:44.540 --> 00:09:48.630
Titan x emits an ultra-long
wavelength vocalization.

92
00:09:49.510 --> 00:09:51.236
and water acts as a conductor.

93
00:09:51.260 --> 00:09:55.196
like whales can communicate
over vast distances.

94
00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:56.656
Like sonar?

95
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.196
Picked it up on outpost 18.

96
00:09:58.220 --> 00:10:01.310
Right. And…

97
00:10:01.890 --> 00:10:02.890
Cate can hear it.

98
00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:10.006
She's sensitive to it in a way that you
and I aren't. and I don't know how or why.

99
00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:14.796
but I was able to make a recording.
using Dr. Suzuki's equipment.

100
00:10:14.820 --> 00:10:17.006
of what it actually sounds like to Cate.

101
00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:18.806
- You recorded it?
- Yes.

102
00:10:18.830 --> 00:10:20.346
You have this recording?

103
00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:22.556
Yes. It's incredible. Lee.

104
00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:25.210
It's the first indication that
the titans have a language.

105
00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:29.066
imagine what that can mean.

106
00:10:29.090 --> 00:10:31.180
Yeah. I'm literally trying to.

107
00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:36.826
What do you mean?

108
00:10:36.850 --> 00:10:39.656
Well. how did you get
that tracker on titan x?

109
00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:44.190
Okay. When suzuki and I were trying
to locate Godzilla with his new device.

110
00:10:44.940 --> 00:10:49.490
he inadvertently. kinda created
this. like. quantum telephone.

111
00:10:54.150 --> 00:10:56.006
When I was in axis mundi.

112
00:10:56.030 --> 00:10:57.426
Keiko!

113
00:10:57.450 --> 00:10:59.240
Run! Run now!

114
00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:16.180
At the same time.

115
00:11:20.010 --> 00:11:21.390
And you knew?

116
00:11:22.060 --> 00:11:23.100
You saw me?

117
00:11:28.690 --> 00:11:30.530
I was waiting for you.

118
00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:34.780
Why didn't you come to me?

119
00:11:36.780 --> 00:11:39.006
Why? We could have
found a way out together.

120
00:11:39.030 --> 00:11:42.016
Kei. the only way I knew
for sure that you'd survive

121
00:11:42.040 --> 00:11:43.290
and get back safely

122
00:11:44.250 --> 00:11:49.056
was if I just let things happen
the way they already had.

123
00:11:49.080 --> 00:11:50.316
That wasn't your choice.

124
00:11:50.340 --> 00:11:52.800
It was my choice to make.

125
00:11:53.340 --> 00:11:55.486
It was my life. it was my future.

126
00:11:55.510 --> 00:11:57.010
and you decided it for me.

127
00:11:58.930 --> 00:12:00.270
What would you have done?

128
00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:05.366
You had no right.

129
00:12:05.390 --> 00:12:06.680
You had no right!

130
00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:08.730
All of this time.

131
00:12:09.770 --> 00:12:11.706
You don't know what could have been.

132
00:12:11.730 --> 00:12:14.006
I could have been there for Hiroshi.

133
00:12:14.030 --> 00:12:15.666
I could have had years with him.

134
00:12:15.690 --> 00:12:17.280
He could still be alive.

135
00:12:21.910 --> 00:12:23.290
That's a lot of "could as."

136
00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:34.146
The neuromuscular response is erratic.

137
00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:35.566
The titan is resisting it.

138
00:12:35.590 --> 00:12:37.066
I mean. we were expecting that.

139
00:12:37.090 --> 00:12:38.840
It wasn't happy about it last time either.

140
00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:41.550
It didn't have an egg to protect then.

141
00:12:42.760 --> 00:12:43.760
That's true.

142
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:48.350
You all right?

143
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:50.730
Is this really necessary?

144
00:12:51.860 --> 00:12:53.610
Kong's eta. six minutes.

145
00:12:54.230 --> 00:12:55.546
There has to be some other way.

146
00:12:55.570 --> 00:12:58.256
Kentaro. if the animal outside is
more important than your father.

147
00:12:58.280 --> 00:13:00.030
you need to tell me right now.

148
00:13:46.030 --> 00:13:47.280
Shit.

149
00:13:52.120 --> 00:13:53.500
Shaw. do you copy?

150
00:13:54.080 --> 00:13:55.566
Dr. Randa?

151
00:13:55.590 --> 00:13:56.720
I just had them.

152
00:13:57.340 --> 00:13:58.486
This island…

153
00:13:58.510 --> 00:14:01.156
Well. if they were headed east.
then they should be right about here.

154
00:14:01.180 --> 00:14:02.606
Stop. stop. stop!

155
00:14:02.630 --> 00:14:04.130
Wait. wait. Stop.

156
00:14:11.690 --> 00:14:13.036
You look like hell.

157
00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:14.600
Good to see you too. may.

158
00:14:15.980 --> 00:14:17.730
- Where did you guys get these?
- Well.

159
00:14:19.940 --> 00:14:23.836
we stole it from the dip shits
that work for Isabel Simmons.

160
00:14:23.860 --> 00:14:26.450
Simmons? As in apex.

161
00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:28.660
Cate and kentaro are with them.

162
00:14:31.040 --> 00:14:32.096
Yeah.

163
00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:34.436
They set up camp at a
decommissioned monarch base

164
00:14:34.460 --> 00:14:36.056
at the end of this valley.

165
00:14:36.080 --> 00:14:37.790
But wait. there's more.

166
00:14:38.840 --> 00:14:40.130
They have the titan.

167
00:14:40.760 --> 00:14:43.236
Well. if you know where
the titan is. we've got a rift.

168
00:14:43.260 --> 00:14:44.316
Let's go to work.

169
00:14:44.340 --> 00:14:45.816
Wait. wait. What do you…

170
00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:47.906
You found the rift? Is it active?

171
00:14:47.930 --> 00:14:49.236
It seems dormant.

172
00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:51.496
but we think titan x's
presence might activate it.

173
00:14:51.520 --> 00:14:53.206
Yeah. but how do we get it there?

174
00:14:53.230 --> 00:14:55.270
Cate and I made a
recording of the titan's song.

175
00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:59.706
We think it may respond
to the sound of its own kind.

176
00:14:59.730 --> 00:15:01.110
- Its own voice.
- Wait. wait.

177
00:15:01.650 --> 00:15:02.716
I'm sorry.

178
00:15:02.740 --> 00:15:05.926
You have a recording
of titans communicating?

179
00:15:05.950 --> 00:15:07.506
Do you have any idea what that means?

180
00:15:07.530 --> 00:15:09.516
- Yes.
- You'd say. because of course

181
00:15:09.540 --> 00:15:10.806
you know what that means.

182
00:15:10.830 --> 00:15:12.170
Gonna need that recording.

183
00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:14.436
Are you sure?

184
00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:15.960
You need to get to your grandkids.

185
00:15:23.760 --> 00:15:25.680
- Good luck.
- You too.

186
00:15:57.540 --> 00:15:58.580
Okay.

187
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:11.180
Pay attention. class.

188
00:16:50.720 --> 00:16:51.760
Slowly.

189
00:18:15.430 --> 00:18:17.100
No! No!

190
00:19:16.070 --> 00:19:17.136
We're too late.

191
00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:19.056
No. that base is built into the Cliffside.

192
00:19:19.080 --> 00:19:21.040
- Cate and kentaro will be safe.
- What about us?

193
00:19:27.130 --> 00:19:28.516
My god.

194
00:19:28.540 --> 00:19:29.870
No. it's Cate.

195
00:19:37.640 --> 00:19:40.366
No. If we get to that base. I
can shut down the synaptic link.

196
00:19:40.390 --> 00:19:42.616
- I gotta go get Cate.
- No. Dr. Ran...

197
00:19:42.640 --> 00:19:44.230
- wait. wait. wait. wait.
- What?

198
00:19:47.810 --> 00:19:48.810
Be careful.

199
00:19:54.780 --> 00:19:56.240
Come on. Let's go!

200
00:21:12.440 --> 00:21:14.280
What happens if Kong wins?

201
00:21:19.860 --> 00:21:22.200
He's standing between a
mother and her child. so…

202
00:21:23.780 --> 00:21:25.240
I know who I'm betting on.

203
00:21:27.160 --> 00:21:29.520
How much farther can you
push it and stay within the limit?

204
00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:33.186
We're… we're almost at the point
where Brenda overloaded the system

205
00:21:33.210 --> 00:21:34.380
in Santa soledad.

206
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:36.250
Almost?

207
00:21:37.210 --> 00:21:39.146
I can give it another 5%.

208
00:21:39.170 --> 00:21:40.170
Do it.

209
00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:11.630
- What's that?
- It's the perimeter sensor.

210
00:22:25.930 --> 00:22:27.326
They're gonna assume
that this was apex.

211
00:22:27.350 --> 00:22:29.326
and my father. he's not gonna
take the blame for us. okay.

212
00:22:29.350 --> 00:22:31.416
He's gonna throw you and me
under the bus. You don't know him.

213
00:22:31.440 --> 00:22:33.940
We're not gonna go around
the world looking for another rift.

214
00:22:34.610 --> 00:22:35.956
This is it.

215
00:22:35.980 --> 00:22:36.980
This is the place.

216
00:22:53.370 --> 00:22:55.686
Fritchman. you secure
the base. Find kentaro.

217
00:22:55.710 --> 00:22:58.590
We're gonna head up to the command
center. which is on the fourth floor.

218
00:22:59.460 --> 00:23:01.486
- Hi. there.
- Don't move.

219
00:23:01.510 --> 00:23:03.486
- No. wait!
- He'll lock us out!

220
00:23:03.510 --> 00:23:04.510
Hey!

221
00:23:11.850 --> 00:23:13.060
Dude.

222
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:18.110
I was a backup punter on
my high school football team.

223
00:23:18.610 --> 00:23:19.756
Yeah.

224
00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:21.320
- Going up?
- Yeah.

225
00:23:22.190 --> 00:23:23.230
Come on.

226
00:23:24.610 --> 00:23:25.650
Find kentaro.

227
00:23:27.570 --> 00:23:28.660
It really hurt.

228
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.400
Cate!

229
00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:17.976
Hey! Hey! Everybody.

230
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:20.396
I need you to step away
from the consoles. please!

231
00:24:20.420 --> 00:24:24.486
I need you to shut down the
synaptic link to that titan immediately.

232
00:24:24.510 --> 00:24:25.986
You want us to step
away from the consoles.

233
00:24:26.010 --> 00:24:27.470
or shut down the link?

234
00:24:29.550 --> 00:24:30.826
All right. All right.

235
00:24:30.850 --> 00:24:31.980
Where's kentaro randa?

236
00:24:34.100 --> 00:24:35.350
Isabel Simmons?

237
00:24:45.780 --> 00:24:47.256
I need you both to come with me now.

238
00:24:47.280 --> 00:24:48.426
Don't worry. He's from monarch.

239
00:24:48.450 --> 00:24:49.620
He's here to help us.

240
00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:53.520
I'm so glad you're here. We
thought you would never come.

241
00:24:54.200 --> 00:24:55.780
Don't worry. You're safe…

242
00:25:03.500 --> 00:25:05.710
May. please. You guys.
over this way. please.

243
00:25:17.730 --> 00:25:20.076
- It's happening again. I can't...
- What? - I can't…

244
00:25:20.100 --> 00:25:22.336
It's locked in a feedback loop.
and it's overloading the system.

245
00:25:22.360 --> 00:25:23.780
Okay. okay. so just turn it off.

246
00:25:32.200 --> 00:25:33.620
It was never the code.

247
00:25:38.790 --> 00:25:42.590
Okay. so how do we unplug a titan?

248
00:25:56.520 --> 00:25:57.900
Cate!

249
00:26:03.270 --> 00:26:04.560
Cate!

250
00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:29.170
Cate! Hang on!

251
00:26:52.400 --> 00:26:53.650
Keiko!

252
00:26:55.990 --> 00:26:57.030
Cate!

253
00:26:58.160 --> 00:27:00.080
Hang on! Got you.

254
00:27:55.550 --> 00:27:57.300
- Come on! Come on!
- Come on. Let's go!

255
00:27:58.930 --> 00:28:00.010
- Come on!
- Tim!

256
00:29:13.800 --> 00:29:17.640
Her instincts are stronger than
any computer code I could write.

257
00:29:21.600 --> 00:29:23.190
She can go home now.

258
00:29:31.520 --> 00:29:33.666
Except she's going the wrong way.

259
00:29:33.690 --> 00:29:34.860
The rift is that way.

260
00:29:35.610 --> 00:29:37.950
Its brain is probably all scrambled.

261
00:29:38.530 --> 00:29:40.530
How are we going to
get it to the rift now?

262
00:30:12.690 --> 00:30:13.860
- Come on!
- Cate!

263
00:30:18.490 --> 00:30:19.620
I gotta go find him.

264
00:30:20.780 --> 00:30:21.950
I have to try.

265
00:30:29.790 --> 00:30:30.790
She better hurry.

266
00:30:46.430 --> 00:30:48.196
- I don't wanna lose you too.
- Look.

267
00:30:48.220 --> 00:30:51.036
I know you've tried to fix
things. but now it's my turn.

268
00:30:51.060 --> 00:30:52.190
Dad's gone.

269
00:30:52.730 --> 00:30:53.956
- We saw him die.
- No.

270
00:30:53.980 --> 00:30:56.036
- We saw a version of him die.
- Stop.

271
00:30:56.060 --> 00:30:57.746
- She's putting ideas in your head.
- Cate.

272
00:30:57.770 --> 00:30:59.270
dad went to axis mundi.

273
00:31:02.820 --> 00:31:04.046
When?

274
00:31:04.070 --> 00:31:05.700
The year we thought he disappeared.

275
00:31:06.240 --> 00:31:07.580
After g-day.

276
00:31:08.290 --> 00:31:09.460
He went into a rift.

277
00:31:10.040 --> 00:31:11.960
Cate. he didn't abandon us.

278
00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:14.370
He was trying to get back to us.

279
00:31:15.500 --> 00:31:18.130
Maybe there's a version of
him still there that I can rescue.

280
00:31:19.300 --> 00:31:21.390
- Why didn't he tell me?
- To protect us.

281
00:31:22.010 --> 00:31:23.090
To keep us safe.

282
00:31:24.340 --> 00:31:25.840
So that we wouldn't follow him.

283
00:31:34.350 --> 00:31:35.350
I don't…

284
00:31:39.820 --> 00:31:41.200
It's impossible.

285
00:31:44.530 --> 00:31:45.860
So was saving you…

286
00:31:55.250 --> 00:31:56.420
Kentaro.

287
00:32:41.210 --> 00:32:42.476
We need to go.

288
00:32:42.500 --> 00:32:43.670
Where's kentaro?

289
00:32:44.340 --> 00:32:45.380
He's not coming.

290
00:32:45.970 --> 00:32:47.140
He's not coming.

291
00:32:50.640 --> 00:32:51.696
Shit.

292
00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.640
Everybody strap in. Let's go!

293
00:33:19.790 --> 00:33:22.226
- Get us in front of her.
- Hang on.

294
00:33:22.250 --> 00:33:23.290
Shit.

295
00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:40.100
There she is.

296
00:33:40.770 --> 00:33:41.996
Is she following us?

297
00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:44.150
No. she's still moving away from the rift.

298
00:33:48.360 --> 00:33:51.280
All right. Let's play the tape.

299
00:34:08.630 --> 00:34:10.276
She can't hear us.

300
00:34:10.300 --> 00:34:11.470
Crank it up louder.

301
00:34:17.470 --> 00:34:19.560
- Louder.
- Cranking it to 11.

302
00:34:32.320 --> 00:34:34.240
I think it's working. She's turning.

303
00:34:44.500 --> 00:34:46.290
- We need to get closer.
- Why?

304
00:34:52.890 --> 00:34:54.310
All right. I'm moving in.

305
00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:24.500
What the hell is going on back there?

306
00:35:27.290 --> 00:35:28.290
Cate?

307
00:35:30.630 --> 00:35:31.670
Cate!

308
00:35:34.050 --> 00:35:35.380
I'll be okay.

309
00:35:39.260 --> 00:35:40.260
I've got you.

310
00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:47.730
All right. Go.

311
00:36:20.810 --> 00:36:22.140
I'm right here.

312
00:36:34.610 --> 00:36:35.610
That's it.

313
00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:38.360
This way.

314
00:36:44.750 --> 00:36:46.556
Lee. hold steady.

315
00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:48.670
That's what I'm trying to do.

316
00:37:03.140 --> 00:37:04.140
This way.

317
00:37:06.100 --> 00:37:08.730
Lee. take us to the rift.

318
00:37:10.020 --> 00:37:11.190
To the rift.

319
00:37:12.520 --> 00:37:13.690
Roger that.

320
00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:38.430
Hey. hold on. This is… this is it?

321
00:37:39.180 --> 00:37:41.576
It doesn't really look
like it's open for business.

322
00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:43.020
It isn't.

323
00:37:57.950 --> 00:37:58.950
Well.

324
00:38:00.110 --> 00:38:01.860
we're about to see if Billy was right.

325
00:38:04.200 --> 00:38:06.450
Hey. what's plan b? Run like hell?

326
00:40:03.990 --> 00:40:05.910
Welcome to the family business.

327
00:40:46.150 --> 00:40:47.190
Lee?

328
00:40:52.540 --> 00:40:54.096
Lee?

329
00:40:54.120 --> 00:40:55.500
What is it. Lee?

330
00:41:27.150 --> 00:41:28.150
Lee.

331
00:41:38.920 --> 00:41:40.896
I can't… I can't… I can't hear you.

332
00:41:40.920 --> 00:41:44.396
What are you saying?
I can't hear you. I…

333
00:41:44.420 --> 00:41:45.896
I can't hear him. What are you saying?

334
00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:48.710
Kei. I was saying…

335
00:43:59.720 --> 00:44:01.850
Dad and monarch
didn't part on best terms.

336
00:44:03.850 --> 00:44:07.270
"In honor of those who
lived by our mission.

337
00:44:07.900 --> 00:44:10.240
Discover and defend."

338
00:44:14.280 --> 00:44:17.490
I think Hiroshi would accept
that as a truthful epitaph.

339
00:44:26.670 --> 00:44:27.710
Hey. Dr. Randa.

340
00:44:30.300 --> 00:44:31.760
You see the one there. top right?

341
00:44:41.600 --> 00:44:44.850
As it were. that might
raise too many questions.

342
00:44:47.770 --> 00:44:49.020
I wanna show you something.

343
00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:56.360
Can you imagine what would happen
if the world found out about you?

344
00:45:00.990 --> 00:45:03.330
We're not the only ones
who know about axis mundi.

345
00:45:06.120 --> 00:45:07.306
Well. can you blame him?

346
00:45:07.330 --> 00:45:09.146
You locked him away for years.

347
00:45:09.170 --> 00:45:10.880
I wasn't talking about Shaw.

348
00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:13.486
I was talking about my
brother and Isabel Simmons

349
00:45:13.510 --> 00:45:15.970
and their insane plan to
rescue my dead father.

350
00:45:18.550 --> 00:45:19.720
Yeah. I…

351
00:45:20.510 --> 00:45:23.496
I assumed that's why
you asked to speak to me.

352
00:45:23.520 --> 00:45:27.616
Or rather demanded
to speak to me today.

353
00:45:27.640 --> 00:45:31.640
You're not gonna stick us in
asset management. are you?

354
00:45:37.400 --> 00:45:38.756
- My left or your left?
- To your left.

355
00:45:38.780 --> 00:45:41.256
- I'm walking backwards.
- Your left. Still to your left.

356
00:45:41.280 --> 00:45:42.886
See? You have to be my eyes.

357
00:45:42.910 --> 00:45:44.386
- I can't see behind me.
- Left.

358
00:45:44.410 --> 00:45:46.136
- My left is not your left…
- wrong. wrong.

359
00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:47.726
- …If I'm going backwards.
- Wrong.

360
00:45:47.750 --> 00:45:49.016
It's the other side.

361
00:45:49.040 --> 00:45:50.606
Hi. You found us.

362
00:45:50.630 --> 00:45:52.380
What exactly have we found?

363
00:45:54.050 --> 00:45:55.606
Monarch 2.0.

364
00:45:55.630 --> 00:45:57.816
More flexible. more nimble.

365
00:45:57.840 --> 00:45:59.276
More plausibly deniable.

366
00:45:59.300 --> 00:46:01.680
That. Back to basics.

367
00:46:02.430 --> 00:46:04.270
Science. Discovery.

368
00:46:05.430 --> 00:46:06.930
Like the founders intended.

369
00:46:07.560 --> 00:46:09.706
This is your way of throwing us a bone?

370
00:46:09.730 --> 00:46:11.876
You just wanna Bury us
out of sight in the basement?

371
00:46:11.900 --> 00:46:13.240
No. no. Not at all.

372
00:46:13.980 --> 00:46:15.900
Ms. Randa. for you.

373
00:46:16.400 --> 00:46:17.900
Doctor. that's for you.

374
00:46:18.700 --> 00:46:20.700
I would like for you
two to run the basement.

375
00:46:21.950 --> 00:46:24.330
I'm sure you know your…
your teammates here.

376
00:46:24.990 --> 00:46:26.700
- Hi.
- Hello.

377
00:46:29.000 --> 00:46:32.356
See. Tim has always talked about
how monarch is a family business.

378
00:46:32.380 --> 00:46:34.566
And kentaro. he is your family.

379
00:46:34.590 --> 00:46:36.276
So. I can't think of anyone better

380
00:46:36.300 --> 00:46:38.930
who can tackle that
very delicate assignment.

381
00:46:41.800 --> 00:46:42.800
Well…

382
00:46:44.470 --> 00:46:45.510
Who needs sunlight?

383
00:46:52.310 --> 00:46:53.900
We have everything we need.

384
00:48:14.650 --> 00:48:16.110
No. no. no. no. no.

385
00:48:16.900 --> 00:48:19.110
We're a long way from even. a-wut.

386
00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:21.310
But…

387
00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.570
Yeah.

388
00:48:41.590 --> 00:48:42.680
Talk to me.

389
00:48:45.840 --> 00:48:46.840
Last night.

390
00:48:48.350 --> 00:48:49.430
two people came by.

391
00:48:50.390 --> 00:48:52.600
A young Japanese man.

392
00:48:53.180 --> 00:48:54.270
American woman.

393
00:48:55.640 --> 00:48:56.760
They were asking about that.

394
00:48:57.730 --> 00:49:00.480
Yeah. well. I seriously hope
you sent them on their way.

395
00:49:01.940 --> 00:49:03.070
That's my business.

396
00:49:05.950 --> 00:49:08.160
I never wanna get into your business

397
00:49:08.740 --> 00:49:11.370
unless I really. really have to.

398
00:49:16.370 --> 00:49:17.450
All right.

399
00:49:18.960 --> 00:49:21.840
They believe that that is the key

400
00:49:22.500 --> 00:49:25.420
to open a door to
everything that they want.

401
00:49:26.300 --> 00:49:29.486
And they're willing to risk
burning the world down to get it.

402
00:49:29.510 --> 00:49:30.760
Trying to play god.

403
00:49:32.470 --> 00:49:33.720
No man should play god.

404
00:49:34.560 --> 00:49:37.400
Hasn't stopped a lot of them
from trying though. has it?

405
00:49:38.900 --> 00:49:39.900
Lee.

406
00:49:43.530 --> 00:49:44.820
Hell no.

407
00:49:45.820 --> 00:49:47.030
So let's go.

408
00:49:48.320 --> 00:49:49.650
Let's do it.

409
00:50:18.480 --> 00:50:19.810
We can't go any further.

410
00:50:23.940 --> 00:50:25.020
A-wut.

411
00:50:26.150 --> 00:50:29.200
is this thing really as bad
as it's cracked up to be?

412
00:51:13.530 --> 00:51:15.030
There you are.

413
00:51:38.680 --> 00:51:40.100
I'll see you soon.
